{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"numclassify","text":"<p>The most comprehensive Python number classification library - 3000+ types, zero dependencies.</p>"},{"location":"#installation","title":"Installation","text":"<pre><code>pip install numclassify\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"#quick-start","title":"Quick Start","text":"<pre><code>import numclassify as nc\nnc.classify(1729)\nnc.classify_batch([6, 28, 496])\nnc.find_by_property(start=1, end=1000, Perfect=True)\nnc.random_number()\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"#why-numclassify","title":"Why numclassify?","text":"<ul> <li>153: Armstrong, Narcissistic, Harshad, Triangular...</li> <li>1729: Taxicab, Carmichael, Dodecagonal...</li> <li>28: Perfect, Triangular, Hexagonal, Keith...</li> </ul> <p>3000+ named number types. Instant lookup. Zero dependencies.</p>"},{"location":"api/","title":"API Reference","text":""},{"location":"api/#classifyn","title":"classify(n)","text":"<p>Returns dict with number, true_properties list, and score.</p>"},{"location":"api/#classify_batchnumbers","title":"classify_batch(numbers)","text":"<p>Classify a list of integers.</p>"},{"location":"api/#random_numbermax_n10000","title":"random_number(max_n=10000)","text":"<p>Classify a random integer up to max_n.</p>"},{"location":"api/#find_by_propertystart-end-filters","title":"find_by_property(start, end, **filters)","text":"<p>Find numbers matching property filters.</p>"},{"location":"api/#streamstart-end","title":"stream(start, end)","text":"<p>Memory-safe generator over large ranges.</p>"},{"location":"api/#registername-category","title":"register(name, category, ...)","text":"<p>Decorator to register custom number types. See examples/custom_type.py.</p>"},{"location":"api/#utilities","title":"Utilities","text":"<ul> <li>get_all_properties(n)</li> <li>get_true_properties(n)</li> <li>print_properties(n)</li> <li>count_properties(n)</li> <li>most_special_in_range(lo, hi)</li> <li>find_in_range(fn, lo, hi)</li> <li>is_prime(n), is_armstrong(n), is_perfect(n)</li> </ul>"},{"location":"changelog/","title":"Changelog","text":"<p>See the full changelog on GitHub.</p>"},{"location":"cli/","title":"CLI Reference","text":""},{"location":"cli/#check","title":"check","text":"<pre><code>numclassify check 1729\nnumclassify check 1729 --json\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"cli/#compare","title":"compare","text":"<pre><code>numclassify compare 6 28\nnumclassify compare 6 28 --json\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"cli/#find","title":"find","text":"<pre><code>numclassify find armstrong --limit 10\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"cli/#range","title":"range","text":"<pre><code>numclassify range 1 100 --filter prime\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"cli/#info","title":"info","text":"<pre><code>numclassify info armstrong\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"cli/#list","title":"list","text":"<pre><code>numclassify list\nnumclassify list --category primes\n</code></pre>"}]}